liberal.title: What Today’s Gun Control Activists Can Learn From Old Battles
liberal.description: In the 1980s, the attempted assassination of President Ronald Reagan and the shooting of his press secretary, Jim Brady, led to a call for gun control. Decades later, students who survived the Parkland, Fla., shooting have reenergized the debate.

conservative.title: Talking Past Each Other on Gun Control
conservative.description: For all the coverage and discussion sparked by the Parkland shooting, the two sides of the debate have retreated to their respective corners.

liberal.title: Trump Stuns Lawmakers With Seeming Embrace of Gun Control Measures

conservative.title: David Hogg Demands $1M Donation From PUBLIX...
conservative.description: David Hogg is trying to shake down Publix. The public face of the gun-control movement demanded $1 million Thursday from the Florida-based grocery chain in a tweet, just one day after calling for a "die-in" protest at its stores.
